(6, 'Kuhusu Sisi', 'About us', 1, '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Lora,serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">UNDP is supporting the Ministry of Energy in implementing Tanzania&rsquo;s first energy efficiency action plan with the support of the European Union (EU). The overall objective of the project is to ensure access to affordable, reliable, sustainable, and modern energy for all in Tanzania. The specific objective is to fast-track a first set of seven (7) key energy efficiency actions and to prepare a comprehensively updated energy efficiency action plan that will be integrated with the Tanzania Energy Efficiency Strategy (TEES) to support the implementation of the national energy policy and strategic goals set by the Tanzania National Development Vision 2025 in terms of ensuring that energy efficiency plays a key role in contributing to the economic and social development of the country.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Lora,serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Lora,serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">The 3-year project, jointly prepared by the Ministry of Energy and UNDP, is expected to help the country in strengthening the legal, regulatory, and institutional frameworks and administrative actions to support implementation and introduction of energy efficiency actions; help large energy consumers and general users to identify and implement quantifiable investments in energy efficiency; help in capacity and skills development, job creation, and increased employability in the energy efficiency and renewable energy services and technology sectors, particularly for women and youth; and increase public awareness, access to information, stakeholder dialogue, and visibility of the financial, economic, and societal benefits of energy efficiency and renewable energy.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Lora,serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">&nbsp;Eight (8) key energy efficiency actions under this project are included: -</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Lora,serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Lora,serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Review and update the Energy Efficiency Action Plan and prepare the Energy Efficiency Strategy to be aligned with the Action Plan</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Lora,serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Development of Minimum Energy Performance Standards (MEPS) and Labelling.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Lora,serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Develop and implement a framework for energy performance certification in large buildings.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Lora,serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Enhancement of Energy Consumption Data of Large Energy Consumers.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Lora,serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Development and implementation of a framework for managing large energy consumers.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Lora,serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Development of professional qualifications and skills in Energy Management and Audit.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Lora,serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">Creation of Energy Efficiency Awareness of the Public.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Lora,serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Lora,serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">EEAP is led by UNDP Tanzania which partners with various other players including Ministry of Energy, the Tanzania Industrial Research and Development Organization (TIRDO), the Tanzania Electrical Supply Company (TANESCO), the Rural Energy Agency (REA), the Tanzania Bureau of Standards (TBS), the Dar es Salaam Institute of Technology (DIT), the Energy and Water Regulatory Authority (EWURA), and the President&rsquo;s Office Regional and Local Government Authority (PO-RALG), National Construction Council (NCC), and others.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Lora,serif\"><span style=\"color:#000000\">UNDP is supporting the Ministry of Energy in implementing Tanzania&rsquo;s first energy efficiency action plan with the support of the European Union (EU). The overall objective of the project is to ensure access to affordable, reliable, sustainable, and modern energy for all in Tanzania. The specific objective is to fast-track a first set of seven (7) key energy efficiency actions and to prepare a comprehensively updated energy efficiency action plan that will be integrated with the Tanzania Energy Efficiency Strategy (TEES) to support the implementation of the national energy policy and strategic goals set by the Tanzania National Development Vision 2025 in terms of ensuring that energy efficiency plays a key role in contributing to the economic and social development of the country.</spa