<p>Main users of EEAP RBS portal are insurers, brokers and all other registrants in the insurance industry that are registered and regulated by the Tanzania Insurance Regulatory Authority.&nbsp; Each of the mentioned registrant appoint one person whose job is to use the portal in accordance with the training given, user credentials and the rights and permissions assigned to him by EEAP RBS Administrator. Through the sub link to EEAP RBS Portal found on RBSS link, the user can access the company&rsquo;s account.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><strong>2.1.2How EEAP RBS Portal is used<\\/strong><\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The regulated insurance companies, brokers and other registrants use EEAP RBS portal to perform the following activities online:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Apply for registration and renewal of insurance business license;<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Submission or reporting of quarterly, semi and annual financial returns;<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Corporate notification of change to corporate structure (Add Director, Add Shareholder, Principal etc.);<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Annual renewal of professional indemnity insurance; and<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Ad-Hoc applications for foreign reinsurance dispensation.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><strong>2.2. EEAP RBS Supervision Centre<\\/strong><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>EEAP RBS Supervision Centre allows EEAP to plan, delegate, track and analyse the entire supervisory process with ease. Core supervisory processes such as Financial Return Submissions, Application Authorizations, Return Analysis and On-Site Inspections are handled and executed at the touch of a button, effectively automating previously arduous and thankless tasks.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><strong>2.2.1. Users of EEAP RBS Supervision Centre<\\/strong><\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The main user of EEAP RBS Supervision Centre is the Authority through its supervisory analysts, insurance officers and other officers in accordance with the training given, user credentials and the rights and permissions assigned to them by EEAP RBS Administrator.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h3><strong>2.2.2. How EEAP RBS Supervision Centre is used<\\/strong><\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The Authority uses EEAP RBS Supervision Centre to perform the following activities online:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul>\\r\\n\\t<li>Schedule and track online data collection activities for the industry;<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Review and approve all data submitted by the industry online;<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Perform detailed analysis on data submitted by the industry online;<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Publish selected reports back to the industry through the system (e.g. market aggregates);<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Schedule on-site inspections to be performed by EEAP staff; and<\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li>Take a risk-based approach to supervision, with automated risk profiling of regulated entities.<\\/li>\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2><strong>2.3.EEAP RBS Repository<\\/strong><\\/h2>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>EEAP RBS Repository safely and securely stores all data related to regulated institutions. The Repository records all institutional profile information, data collected from regulated institutions and analytical data generated by the regulator. A complete system-wide audit trail is also maintained. Its is fully searchable giving you access to an unparalleled amount of regulatory and supervisory information, all in one place.<\\/p>\",\"photo_url\":\"a4e9a3a9a6d71c0a2440aab1d42e62ca.jpeg\",\"featured\":0,\"active\":\"1\",\"slug\":\"demo-service\",\"call_to_action_en\":\"Go to Service Now\",\"call_to_action_sw\":\"Ingia Sasa\",\"url\":null,\"created_at\":\"2022-03-07T11:01:23.000000Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2022-06-30T20:26:02.000000Z\",\"user_id\":0,\"icon\":\"icon-1659878528\",\"color\":null,\"specials\":null}', '2022-08-07 10:22:08', '2022-08-07 10:22:08'),
