(2758, 1, 'News', 'store', '41.59.81.108', 'https://www.eeap.go.tz/cms/news', '{\"title_en\":\"Meeting to receive and hear insurance complaints held in the central zone - Dodoma\",\"title_sw\":\"Mkutano wa kupokea na kusikiliza malalamiko ya Bima uliofanyika kanda ya kati - Dodoma .\",\"content_en\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:12.0pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\\\">The Tanzania Insurance Regulatory Authority (EEAP) on 27.04.2023 organized a meeting to receive and hear insurance complaints held in the central zone - Dodoma at Morena Hotel.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:12.0pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\\\">In the picture sitting is the Chairperson of the meeting and also the Insurance Ambassador Eng. Zena Said (General Secretary and the Secretary of the Revolutionary Government of Zanzibar) center, Commissioner of Insurance Dr. Baghayo A. Saqware third right, Deputy Commissioner of Insurance Khadija I. Said third left, EEAP Central zone Manager Mr. Shaarif Hamad first right, Representative of Insurance Companies Ms. Merina Hussein first left, Hon. Wanu Hafidh Member of Parliament and Ambassador of Insurance second right and Hon. Josephat Hassunga Member of Parliament and Insurance Ambassador second left. Those&nbsp;who stood are the Management of the Tanzania Insurance Regulatory Authority (EEAP).<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:12.0pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\\\">The meeting was held as a continuation of the meetings to receive and listen to insurance complaints in the country which the Authority has been conducting with the aims of receiving and resolving the various challenges facing insurance consumers and stakeholders, getting feedback and advice from insurance users, insurance providers, and insurance beneficiaries.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:12.0pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\\\">For his part, Commissioner of Insurance Dr. Baghayo Saqware told the participants that it is important to discuss and cooperate in developing the insurance market. It is also a prospect of EEAP continuing to address citizens&#39; complaints of insurance users and policy complaints the authority will continue to advise the government. He also issued directives to insurance players to address and handle the complaints of insurance consumers in accordance with the laws, regulations, and various guidelines issued by the Authority. Finally, he insisted that EEAP is ready to continue receiving and addressing the complaints, comments, and advice of insurance stakeholders with the aim of promoting and developing the insurance sector in the country.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:12.0pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\\\">In addition, Hon. Josephat Hassunga Member of Parliament of the Republic and Insurance Ambassador insisted participants and citizens use insurance services to protect themselves from various disasters and risks. He also insisted that it is important to accelerate the provision of insurance awareness for citizens, especially in rural areas in order to promote the insurance sector.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:12.0pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\\\">&nbsp;In concluding remarks, a Chairperson of the meeting Eng. Zena Said (General Secretary and the Secretary of the revolutionary government of Zanzibar) insisted that it is important for government institutions to collaborate to deliver quality services to the people and grow the overall GDP. She also directed the Authority (EEAP) to continue to uphold the rights of insurance consumers and providers in accordance with various laws, regulations, and guidelines, as well as to accelerate the provision of insurance awareness to citizens especially in rural areas. Finally, she congratulated EEAP for the various efforts for &nbsp;being made to promote and develop the insurance market including organizing such meetings.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<div>\\r\\n<hr \\/>\\r\\n<div>\\r\\n<div class=\\\"msocomtxt\\\" id=\\\"_com_1\\\">&nbsp;<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\\r\\n<\\/div>\",\"content_sw\":\"<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:12.0pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\\\">Mamlaka ya Usimamizi wa Bima Tanzania (EEAP)&nbsp; &nbsp;tarehe 27.04.2023 iliandaa mkutano wa kupokea na kusikiliza malalamiko ya Bima uliofanyika kanda ya kati - Dodoma katika ukumbi wa Morena Hoteli.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:12.0pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\\\">Pichani waliokaa ni Mwenyekiti wa Mkutano huo na pia Balozi wa bima nchini Mhandisi. Zena Said (Katibu Mkuu Kiongozi na Katibu Mkuu wa Baraza la Mapinduzi Zaznibar) katikati, Kamishna wa Bima Tanzania Dkt. Baghayo A. Sagware wa tatu kulia, Naibu Kamishna wa Bima Bi. Khadija I. Said wa tatu kushoto, Meneja wa Kanda ya Kati wa EEAP Bw. Shaarif Hamad wa kwanza kulia, Mwakilishi wa Makampuni ya Bima Bi. Merina Hussein wa kwanza kushoto, Mhe. Wanu Hafidh Mbunge wa Jamhuri na Balozi wa Bima nchini wa pili kulia na Mhe. Josephat Hassunga Mbunge wa Jamhuri na Balozi wa Bima nchini wa pili kushoto. Waliosimama ni&nbsp; &nbsp;Menejimenti ya Mamlaka ya Usimamizi wa Bima Tanzania (EEAP).<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:12.0pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\\\">Mkutano huo umefanyika ikiwa ni mwendelezo wa mikutano ya kupokea na kusikiliza malalamiko ya Bima nchini ambapo Mamlaka imekuwa ikifanya kwa lengo la kupokea na kutatua changamoto mbalimbali wanazozipata wadau watumiaji wa bima nchini, kupata maoni na ushauri ya wadau watumiaji wa bima, watoa huduma za bima na wananchi wanufaika wa bima.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:12.0pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\\\">Kwa upande wake, Kamishna wa Bima Dkt. Baghayo Saqware, aliwaeleza washiriki kwamba ni muhimu kujadiliana na kushirikiana katika kukuza soko la Bima. Aidha ni matarajio ya EEAP kuendelea kushughulikia malalamiko ya wananchi watumiaji wa bima na malalamiko ya kisera mamlaka itaendelea kuishauri serikali. Pia alitoa rai kwa watoa huduma za bima kushughulikia malalamiko ya wananchi watumiaji wa bima kulingana na sheria, kanuni na kwa kufuata miongozo mbalimbali inayotolewa na Mamlaka. Mwisho kabisa, alisisitiza kuwa EEAP ipo tayari kuendelea kupokea na kuyashughulikia malalamiko, maoni na ushauri wa wadau wa Bima kwa lengo la kukuza na kuendeleza sekta ya bima nchini.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:12.0pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\\\">Aidha, Mhe. Josephat Hassunga Mbunge wa Jamhuri na Balozi wa Bima alitoa maelekezo &nbsp;kwa washiriki na wananchi kutumia huduma za bima ili kujikinga na majanga na maafa mbalimbali yanapotokea. Pia alisisitiza kuwa ni muhimu kuongeza kasi ya utoaji wa elimu ya Bima kwa wananchi hasa vijijini ili kukuza sekta ya bima.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"text-align:justify\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:11pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:12.0pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\\\">Kwa upande wake, Mwenyekiti wa mkutano huo ambaye pia ni Balozi wa bima nchini Mhandisi. Zena Said (Katibu Mkuu Kiongozi na Katibu wa Baraza la Mapinduzi Zanzibar) alisisitiza kuwa ni muhimu kwa Taasisi za Serikali kushirikiana kwa pamoja katika kutoa huduma bora kwa wananchi na kukuza pato la Taifa kwa ujumla. Aidha alielekeza Mamlaka (EEAP) kuendelea kusimamia haki za watumiaji na watoa huduma za bima kulingana na sheria, kanuni na miongozo mbalimbali, pia kuongeza kasi ya utoaji wa elimu ya bima kwa wananchi hasa vijijini. Mwisho kabisa, aliipongeza EEAP kwa juhudi mbalimbali zinazofanyika katika kukuza na kuendeleza soko la bima ikiwemo kuandaa mikutano ya namna hii.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\",\"active\":\"1\",\"photo_url\":\"706f3cbc2e86ea2db9115af96762fe4a.jpeg\",\"user_id\":1,\"slug\":\"meeting-to-receive-and-hear-insurance-complaints-held-in-the-central-zone-dodoma\"}', '2023-05-04 04:14:39', '2023-05-04 04:14:39'),
